WEBVTT

00:05.000 --> 00:12.500
The next part of our program will be an analysis of what tools we have to stimulate labor,

00:12.500 --> 00:18.500
and there are not so many of them, and what combinations can be made of this, and what we get as a result.

00:18.500 --> 00:26.500
So, let's take a closer look at the tools that we, as managers, have in stock

00:26.500 --> 00:32.500
in order to form a compensation plan that is attractive to our employees.

00:32.500 --> 00:42.500
A compensation plan is a house of cubes that our employee should like.

00:42.500 --> 00:51.500
Our employees are different, so we will provide different compensation plans to different employees,

00:51.500 --> 00:58.500
in order to stimulate their behavior, which is required of these employees for our company.

00:58.500 --> 01:04.500
But there are relatively few cubes from which these plans are made.

01:04.500 --> 01:12.500
Let's start with the fact that all these components of the compensation plan, all these cubes, can be divided into two categories.

01:12.500 --> 01:18.500
The first category is direct payments, that is, this is the money that our employees receive

01:18.500 --> 01:26.500
as compensation for working at our enterprise, giving us their time, energy, strength, knowledge, and so on.

01:26.500 --> 01:31.500
The second category is what is commonly called a social package.

01:31.500 --> 01:38.500
At first glance, the social package is not very related to stimulating labor.

01:38.500 --> 01:49.500
As a rule, it is not money, it is either a guarantee, or a compensation, or goods and services that the enterprise provides to its employees.

01:49.500 --> 01:58.500
Nevertheless, if we look at the most advanced and developed organizations, they have a large and rather complex social package.

01:58.500 --> 02:05.500
Let's take a separate look at the components of the social package and try to understand why it is needed and how to design it.

02:06.500 --> 02:08.500
Let's start with direct payments.

02:08.500 --> 02:12.500
Direct payments are also divided into two parts.

02:12.500 --> 02:22.500
The first part is the permanent part, that is, what our employee receives every month, regardless of how he worked.

02:22.500 --> 02:28.500
The second part is the variable part, which is the part that the employee receives to a greater or lesser extent,

02:28.500 --> 02:34.500
in connection with a particular collective or individual result.

02:34.500 --> 02:36.500
Let's start with the permanent part.

02:36.500 --> 02:42.500
At most enterprises, there is a thing called a positional package.

02:42.500 --> 02:50.500
To do this, a tariff grid is developed, that is, a table that shows which category of employees is subject to which package.

02:50.500 --> 03:01.500
As a rule, the tariff grid and its categories have a certain width, which is called a conditional fork.

03:01.500 --> 03:09.500
That is, within each category there is a minimum, a median, an average and a maximum part.

03:09.500 --> 03:13.500
We will look at how the tariff grid is formed separately.

03:13.500 --> 03:16.500
The second part is personal add-ons.

03:16.500 --> 03:26.500
In the case when a given employee does not pay the tariff grid according to his merits and values for the organization,

03:26.500 --> 03:31.500
we can offer him additional monetary rewards.

03:31.500 --> 03:35.500
For what? For the experience of working in our company.

03:35.500 --> 03:44.500
There are companies that add money to the old employees for remaining loyal to the enterprise.

03:44.500 --> 03:49.500
The more employees remain at the enterprise, the more these add-ons.

03:49.500 --> 03:52.500
Maybe for special knowledge and qualifications.

03:52.500 --> 03:58.500
Let's imagine that our organization actively works with representatives of different countries,

03:58.500 --> 04:03.500
and we need managers who can communicate in Chinese, Japanese, Hindi, etc.

04:03.500 --> 04:08.500
We can pay people for mastering rare foreign languages.

04:08.500 --> 04:11.500
I will say only one thing about add-ons.

04:11.500 --> 04:19.500
This is a very useful thing, because it individualizes the attitude of the employer to the employee.

04:19.500 --> 04:25.500
It shows the employee his personal, individual value for the organization.

04:25.500 --> 04:29.500
But I do not recommend getting too involved in add-ons,

04:29.500 --> 04:34.500
because it often turns out that all the order in the labor payment,

04:34.500 --> 04:40.500
which we tried to establish with the help of the tariff grid and the construction of premium rewards,

04:40.500 --> 04:44.500
is interrupted by a huge number of add-ons, which are purely individual,

04:44.500 --> 04:49.500
and as a result, the whole system loses its controllability, clarity and integrity.

04:49.500 --> 04:54.500
And finally, the constant part is the compensation for the worker's expenses.

04:54.500 --> 04:56.500
What is it?

04:56.500 --> 05:02.500
Imagine that we have several drivers on our personal cars.

05:02.500 --> 05:08.500
Of course, they spend money on the service, on technical inspection, on repair, on gasoline.

05:08.500 --> 05:17.500
These are the personal funds that a person, due to his position and role, invests in the work of our enterprise.

05:17.500 --> 05:22.500
Naturally, it would be fair if the enterprise compensated him for this money.

05:22.500 --> 05:24.500
The variable part.

05:24.500 --> 05:32.500
The variable part includes two components, one of which is called premiums, and the other is called bonuses.

05:32.500 --> 05:34.500
These terms are often confused.

05:34.500 --> 05:37.500
I propose to define them this way.

05:37.500 --> 05:43.500
The premium is what is relatively small in relation to the deposit,

05:43.500 --> 05:48.500
well, the maximum is 100%, no more than the deposit.

05:48.500 --> 05:52.500
And it is paid often, at a certain period of time.

05:52.500 --> 05:57.500
It is paid either once a month or once a quarter.

05:57.500 --> 05:59.500
What are bonuses?

05:59.500 --> 06:08.500
A bonus is a reward that is paid rarely, usually once a year, and it is large in relation to the deposit.

06:08.500 --> 06:12.500
For example, it can reach 10, 12 deposits.

06:12.500 --> 06:20.500
Bonuses are a significant expense for an enterprise due to their size.

06:20.500 --> 06:25.500
Therefore, it is not always advisable to pay them to all categories of workers.

06:26.500 --> 06:29.500
This system is not always effective.

06:29.500 --> 06:34.500
What categories of workers should be paid to, and why, we will find out in the third part of the course,

06:34.500 --> 06:38.500
when we will consider specific situations and cases.

06:38.500 --> 06:44.500
These are all the cubes from which we can draw up compensation plans.

06:44.500 --> 06:48.500
It seems that there are not so many of them, and the picture is quite simple.

06:48.500 --> 06:50.500
But this is only at first glance.

06:50.500 --> 06:55.500
Now we will consider these components of the compensation plan separately.

06:55.500 --> 07:00.500
We will try to understand the logic by which they are built, how they work,

07:00.500 --> 07:04.500
and what we need to do to make them all work effectively at our enterprise.

07:04.500 --> 07:11.500
Each of the components of the compensation plan has its own purpose in the incentive system.

07:12.500 --> 07:20.500
Let's consider them separately and try to understand what we want to achieve from the worker

07:20.500 --> 07:26.500
using each of these cubes or bricks that we have just discussed.

07:26.500 --> 07:29.500
The first one.

07:29.500 --> 07:34.500
The permanent part of the compensation plan, that is, the duty deposit,

07:34.500 --> 07:40.500
is aimed at providing the level of life that the worker would like to maintain.

07:40.500 --> 07:47.500
We remember that this is one of the most important factors in the worker's attitude to the incentive system.

07:47.500 --> 07:48.500
The second one.

07:48.500 --> 07:51.500
The permanent part provides the worker with loyalty,

07:51.500 --> 07:54.500
because he knows that he will receive it tomorrow and the day after tomorrow,

07:54.500 --> 07:59.500
and in the future, he will be given a promotion under good conditions.

07:59.500 --> 08:10.500
This is a feeling of confidence in the future and loyalty to our employee at the enterprise.

08:10.500 --> 08:18.500
And finally, the permanent part, due to its size, is our message to the worker,

08:18.500 --> 08:24.500
our signal to him that we highly appreciate his work.

08:24.500 --> 08:28.500
The high permanent part, high duty deposits,

08:28.500 --> 08:33.500
is a demonstration from the employer that the worker is appreciated by the organization.

08:33.500 --> 08:38.500
Again, we see a mix of moral and material factors of the incentive system.

08:38.500 --> 08:39.500
The variable part.

08:39.500 --> 08:43.500
As we have already seen, the variable part includes two components,

08:43.500 --> 08:45.500
that is, bonuses and bonuses.

08:45.500 --> 08:50.500
The bonuses are primarily the incentives for short-term results.

08:50.500 --> 08:52.500
What do I mean by short-term?

08:52.500 --> 08:55.500
Since they are paid out quite often,

08:55.500 --> 08:58.500
this is a signal to the worker that he has done a good job.

08:58.500 --> 09:00.500
But not only that.

09:00.500 --> 09:02.500
If the worker has done a bad job,

09:02.500 --> 09:03.500
violated the rules,

09:03.500 --> 09:06.500
did not bring the results we expected from him,

09:06.500 --> 09:09.500
then we can reduce this bonus.

09:09.500 --> 09:13.500
And in this case, if we talk in the format of a wick and a gingerbread,

09:13.500 --> 09:17.500
then the bonus is not only a gingerbread,

09:17.500 --> 09:20.500
but also the possibility of using a wick, if you want.

09:20.500 --> 09:25.500
That is, if there is a high premium component in the compensation plan,

09:25.500 --> 09:29.500
it can be used as a punishment for the worker.

09:29.500 --> 09:31.500
That is, to deprive him.

09:31.500 --> 09:32.500
Bonuses.

09:32.500 --> 09:36.500
Bonuses provide several factors at once.

09:36.500 --> 09:40.500
First of all, it is a guarantee of loyalty,

09:40.500 --> 09:42.500
a guarantee of prospects,

09:42.500 --> 09:46.500
because if a person knows that at the end of the year he will receive a large amount,

09:46.500 --> 09:49.500
then, accordingly, he will probably work this year

09:49.500 --> 09:51.500
and will not leave us.

09:51.500 --> 09:54.500
The second is the stimulation of long-term results,

09:54.500 --> 09:55.500
unlike the premium.

09:55.500 --> 09:58.500
There are a number of positions, especially top ones,

09:58.500 --> 10:03.500
where it is impossible to achieve results within a month or a quarter.

10:03.500 --> 10:06.500
The results are visible only at the level of the company as a whole,

10:06.500 --> 10:08.500
in the long term.

10:08.500 --> 10:13.500
And, accordingly, bonuses support this work for the long term.

10:13.500 --> 10:16.500
And finally, bonuses play the role of moral support,

10:16.500 --> 10:18.500
of course, very strong,

10:18.500 --> 10:21.500
because it is a very powerful signal to organizations and workers

10:21.500 --> 10:23.500
that they are valuable to them.

10:23.500 --> 10:26.500
I know organizations where workers say,

10:26.500 --> 10:28.500
well, our salary is not very high,

10:28.500 --> 10:32.500
but we work mainly for bonuses.

10:32.500 --> 10:35.500
And finally, the social package.

10:35.500 --> 10:38.500
The social package solves several problems at once.

10:38.500 --> 10:42.500
First, it contributes to the level of support

10:42.500 --> 10:46.500
of the level of life of the workers to which they are oriented.

10:47.500 --> 10:50.500
Second, it provides loyalty.

10:50.500 --> 10:53.500
And, on the other hand, it demonstrates to workers

10:53.500 --> 10:55.500
that the organization is promising

10:55.500 --> 10:57.500
and is going to work further,

10:57.500 --> 10:59.500
and will not leave the market,

10:59.500 --> 11:01.500
and will not be kicked out of work.

11:01.500 --> 11:03.500
If the organization invests in the social package,

11:03.500 --> 11:06.500
it demonstrates its stability.

11:07.500 --> 11:11.500
Of course, the social package plays a significant moral role,

11:12.500 --> 11:15.500
because it demonstrates the employer's work,

11:15.500 --> 11:17.500
the care for its employees.

11:19.500 --> 11:21.500
How does this happen?

11:21.500 --> 11:23.500
We will see a little later.

11:23.500 --> 11:25.500
Now I will say only one thing.

11:25.500 --> 11:29.500
An effective system of stimulation of labor

11:29.500 --> 11:33.500
requires us to design our house,

11:33.500 --> 11:36.500
or a set of houses of different compensation plans,

11:36.500 --> 11:39.500
depending on what we are, first of all,

11:39.500 --> 11:42.500
and what categories of workers we expect.

11:42.500 --> 11:45.500
Providing them with the right standard of living,

11:45.500 --> 11:48.500
prospects, attachment to our organization,

11:48.500 --> 11:51.500
stimulating short-term results,

11:51.500 --> 11:54.500
or stimulating long-term results,

11:54.500 --> 11:56.500
and moral factors,

11:56.500 --> 11:58.500
that is, demonstrations to our workers,

11:58.500 --> 12:01.500
our mutual loyalty to them.

12:02.500 --> 12:05.500
There are several standard,

12:05.500 --> 12:07.500
widely known around the world,

12:07.500 --> 12:10.500
traditional compensation plans,

12:10.500 --> 12:13.500
which I would like to start with.

12:15.500 --> 12:18.500
The first thing to say in this regard is the question

12:18.500 --> 12:21.500
of what we will put as the basis

12:21.500 --> 12:24.500
of what we are going to pay the worker.

12:24.500 --> 12:26.500
There are two approaches.

12:26.500 --> 12:29.500
We will pay one worker their result.

12:30.500 --> 12:34.500
If it is a machine that produces parts,

12:34.500 --> 12:38.500
we want to pay him for a certain amount of parts,

12:38.500 --> 12:42.500
produced in a certain amount of time and without defects.

12:42.500 --> 12:44.500
If it is a sales manager,

12:44.500 --> 12:47.500
we want to pay him for how many clients he attracted,

12:47.500 --> 12:49.500
how much goods he let go,

12:49.500 --> 12:52.500
what amount, what is his turnover,

12:52.500 --> 12:54.500
that is, we pay according to the results.

12:55.500 --> 12:58.500
The second payment system is temporary.

12:58.500 --> 13:00.500
This means that we pay the worker

13:00.500 --> 13:02.500
for the time spent at work,

13:02.500 --> 13:05.500
provided that he was not just sitting on a chair,

13:05.500 --> 13:07.500
but was doing something.

13:08.500 --> 13:11.500
There are also mixed forms of labor payment,

13:11.500 --> 13:14.500
which we will talk about in more detail.

13:14.500 --> 13:17.500
I want to say right away that we can pay

13:17.500 --> 13:19.500
each worker separately,

13:19.500 --> 13:21.500
according to his results or his time,

13:21.500 --> 13:24.500
or we can use collective or brigade forms

13:24.500 --> 13:26.500
of labor payment,

13:26.500 --> 13:30.500
when the result, time, or labor of the worker is paid,

13:30.500 --> 13:34.500
and within it there is already a distribution of payment

13:34.500 --> 13:36.500
among the workers.

13:36.500 --> 13:39.500
So let's start with the payment according to the results.

13:39.500 --> 13:41.500
It is called a collective payment,

13:41.500 --> 13:44.500
and there are quite a few options.

13:44.500 --> 13:47.500
The first is called a simple collective payment,

13:47.500 --> 13:49.500
and in Russian it is called

13:49.500 --> 13:51.500
as you dig, so you dig.

13:51.500 --> 13:55.500
This means that if I stand by the conveyor

13:55.500 --> 13:58.500
and collect the devices,

13:58.500 --> 14:01.500
then from each device I have collected

14:01.500 --> 14:04.500
and left my workplace further along the conveyor,

14:04.500 --> 14:07.500
I get a certain amount of money.

14:07.500 --> 14:09.500
How much is calculated separately

14:09.500 --> 14:12.500
depends on the complexity of the work I do,

14:12.500 --> 14:14.500
the cost of this device,

14:14.500 --> 14:17.500
the risks, and a number of factors.

14:17.500 --> 14:19.500
Strictly speaking, this is a case

14:19.500 --> 14:22.500
when I do not have a permanent part of the labor payment,

14:22.500 --> 14:24.500
but there is how much I have done,

14:24.500 --> 14:27.500
or the same can be said about sales managers,

14:27.500 --> 14:30.500
we know that the system is quite widespread

14:30.500 --> 14:33.500
when a person does not receive anything from the organization

14:33.500 --> 14:35.500
except a percentage of sales,

14:35.500 --> 14:37.500
expressed in some units.

14:37.500 --> 14:40.500
It seems that a simple collective payment

14:40.500 --> 14:43.500
is simple, obvious, and very transparent.

14:43.500 --> 14:46.500
In fact, it has a number of disadvantages,

14:46.500 --> 14:49.500
starting with the fact that it does not provide

14:49.500 --> 14:52.500
social protection for the worker,

14:52.500 --> 14:55.500
it does not provide workers with confidence

14:55.500 --> 14:57.500
in the future,

14:57.500 --> 15:00.500
it does not show a positive attitude

15:00.500 --> 15:03.500
to the worker from the enterprise,

15:03.500 --> 15:05.500
and besides, between us,

15:05.500 --> 15:08.500
a simple collective payment allows

15:08.500 --> 15:11.500
a number of underground, under the carpet options

15:11.500 --> 15:13.500
how it can be managed.

15:13.500 --> 15:16.500
For example, the valuation of the same work

15:16.500 --> 15:18.500
can be raised or reduced.

15:18.500 --> 15:21.500
For example, a foreman who determines

15:21.500 --> 15:23.500
how many workers did,

15:23.500 --> 15:26.500
can only describe a small number of workers.

15:26.500 --> 15:29.500
In short, it is not so simple,

15:29.500 --> 15:31.500
not so beautiful,

15:31.500 --> 15:33.500
not so transparent.

15:33.500 --> 15:36.500
Therefore, for the vast majority of enterprises,

15:36.500 --> 15:38.500
including sales,

15:38.500 --> 15:41.500
today they refuse this simple collective payment.

15:41.500 --> 15:44.500
I must add one more major drawback

15:44.500 --> 15:46.500
of the collective payment.

15:46.500 --> 15:48.500
As soon as the worker is offered

15:48.500 --> 15:50.500
other valuations in another place,

15:50.500 --> 15:52.500
he also goes there with pleasure.

15:52.500 --> 15:55.500
There is a collective premium form of payment.

15:55.500 --> 15:58.500
This is when, in addition to the payment

15:58.500 --> 16:00.500
for the output or the results,

16:00.500 --> 16:02.500
bonuses are added for quality,

16:02.500 --> 16:04.500
for speed,

16:04.500 --> 16:06.500
for what we agreed with the worker.

16:06.500 --> 16:09.500
This is a more progressive form of labor payment,

16:09.500 --> 16:11.500
because it really performs

16:11.500 --> 16:14.500
a stimulating function for the worker.

16:14.500 --> 16:17.500
There is also a collective progressive form

16:17.500 --> 16:19.500
of labor payment.

16:19.500 --> 16:20.500
What is it?

16:20.500 --> 16:22.500
This form is used in cases

16:22.500 --> 16:24.500
when we need to complete the work

16:24.500 --> 16:26.500
as quickly as possible.

16:26.500 --> 16:28.500
We have an urgent order,

16:28.500 --> 16:31.500
and we need our workers to come out

16:31.500 --> 16:34.500
in time, for which we will pay them separately,

16:34.500 --> 16:36.500
and to cope with the production

16:36.500 --> 16:39.500
of the above-mentioned product as quickly as possible.

16:39.500 --> 16:41.500
Or, let's assume that we have a warehouse

16:41.500 --> 16:44.500
full of goods that need to be liquidated urgently.

16:44.500 --> 16:47.500
We can, of course, reduce the cost of goods,

16:47.500 --> 16:50.500
but this is not always profitable.

16:50.500 --> 16:52.500
Maybe it is more profitable for us

16:52.500 --> 16:54.500
to pay our sellers

16:54.500 --> 16:56.500
to work more intensively

16:56.500 --> 16:58.500
and to invest in the specified period.

16:58.500 --> 17:00.500
In this case, there is a collective

17:00.500 --> 17:02.500
progressive form of labor payment,

17:02.500 --> 17:04.500
which means that my workers

17:04.500 --> 17:06.500
get a big bonus if they cope

17:06.500 --> 17:08.500
with the work within the period

17:08.500 --> 17:10.500
we gave them.

17:10.500 --> 17:12.500
The next form of collective payment

17:12.500 --> 17:14.500
is accord payment.

17:14.500 --> 17:16.500
What is accord?

17:16.500 --> 17:18.500
It is when the payment is made

17:18.500 --> 17:21.500
not based on the number of produced parts,

17:21.500 --> 17:23.500
not on the number of sold goods,

17:23.500 --> 17:25.500
but on the performance of a certain,

17:25.500 --> 17:27.500
usually large, amount of work.

17:27.500 --> 17:29.500
In this context, accord payment

17:29.500 --> 17:31.500
is often used in a brigade

17:31.500 --> 17:33.500
or collective form,

17:33.500 --> 17:36.500
when a team, a team or a team,

17:36.500 --> 17:38.500
takes on the performance

17:38.500 --> 17:40.500
of a certain amount of work,

17:40.500 --> 17:42.500
and as a result,

17:42.500 --> 17:44.500
they receive the amount of money

17:44.500 --> 17:47.500
they agreed to pay to the employer.

17:47.500 --> 17:49.500
The simplest examples are

17:49.500 --> 17:51.500
when you hire a brigade

17:51.500 --> 17:53.500
to build a cottage.

17:53.500 --> 17:55.500
As a result of this work,

17:55.500 --> 17:58.500
you have to pay a certain amount of money

17:58.500 --> 18:00.500
to the building.

18:00.500 --> 18:02.500
It seems that this accord system

18:02.500 --> 18:04.500
is old and primitive,

18:04.500 --> 18:06.500
and it is mainly related

18:06.500 --> 18:08.500
to relatively simple types of labor.

18:08.500 --> 18:10.500
No, it is not.

18:10.500 --> 18:12.500
The same system is used

18:12.500 --> 18:15.500
in the payment of project management.

18:15.500 --> 18:17.500
When a project is implemented,

18:17.500 --> 18:19.500
no matter in what field,

18:19.500 --> 18:21.500
in the field of implementation,

18:21.500 --> 18:23.500
in the field of development,

18:23.500 --> 18:25.500
in the field of IT,

18:25.500 --> 18:27.500
in the field of design,

18:27.500 --> 18:29.500
a temporary team is created,

18:29.500 --> 18:31.500
a team, as they say,

18:31.500 --> 18:33.500
and this team works

18:33.500 --> 18:35.500
until the result is achieved,

18:35.500 --> 18:37.500
according to which

18:37.500 --> 18:39.500
this accord payment is received.

18:40.500 --> 18:42.500
There is also a well-known

18:42.500 --> 18:44.500
accord-premium system.

18:44.500 --> 18:46.500
This is when we not only agree

18:46.500 --> 18:48.500
to perform a certain amount of work,

18:48.500 --> 18:50.500
but also guarantee a higher premium

18:50.500 --> 18:52.500
if, as in the case of a

18:52.500 --> 18:54.500
production-progressive system,

18:54.500 --> 18:56.500
the work is done on time,

18:56.500 --> 18:58.500
a short period of time,

18:58.500 --> 19:00.500
as a rule,

19:00.500 --> 19:02.500
and with high quality.

19:02.500 --> 19:04.500
Temporary payment.

19:04.500 --> 19:06.500
At first glance,

19:06.500 --> 19:08.500
it seems more primitive,

19:09.500 --> 19:11.500
less stimulating than

19:11.500 --> 19:13.500
the actual payment.

19:13.500 --> 19:15.500
But let's look at the

19:15.500 --> 19:17.500
members of our employees,

19:17.500 --> 19:19.500
their role and functions.

19:19.500 --> 19:21.500
We have employees who

19:21.500 --> 19:23.500
clearly give a specific result,

19:23.500 --> 19:25.500
which can be calculated in rubles

19:25.500 --> 19:27.500
or in other units.

19:27.500 --> 19:29.500
And there are employees whose

19:29.500 --> 19:31.500
task is to ensure the process.

19:31.500 --> 19:33.500
The most striking

19:33.500 --> 19:35.500
manifestation is accounting.

19:35.500 --> 19:37.500
They do not give results

19:37.500 --> 19:39.500
but must perform their functions

19:39.500 --> 19:41.500
accurately and on time.

19:41.500 --> 19:43.500
Or, in the structure of your HR

19:43.500 --> 19:45.500
management, there is a recruiter,

19:45.500 --> 19:47.500
whose mission is to hire

19:47.500 --> 19:49.500
employees and fill vacancies.

19:49.500 --> 19:51.500
We can calculate how many

19:51.500 --> 19:53.500
employees he hired and what

19:53.500 --> 19:55.500
terms they served.

19:55.500 --> 19:57.500
And next to him or in the next

19:57.500 --> 19:59.500
room sits an inspector on duty,

19:59.500 --> 20:01.500
whose task is to provide

20:01.500 --> 20:03.500
the documents on time.

20:03.500 --> 20:05.500
So, temporary payment

20:05.500 --> 20:07.500
is used for those categories

20:07.500 --> 20:09.500
of employees for which it is

20:09.500 --> 20:11.500
impossible or difficult to

20:11.500 --> 20:13.500
calculate specific results.

20:13.500 --> 20:15.500
But it exists as a simple

20:15.500 --> 20:17.500
temporariness.

20:17.500 --> 20:19.500
The most primitive case is

20:19.500 --> 20:21.500
when we pay the employee

20:21.500 --> 20:23.500
the same amount of hours

20:23.500 --> 20:25.500
they have worked,

20:25.500 --> 20:27.500
in accordance with the tariff grid.

20:27.500 --> 20:29.500
It is clear that this form

20:29.500 --> 20:31.500
does not stimulate the work too much,

20:31.500 --> 20:33.500
so there is a temporary payment

20:33.500 --> 20:35.500
form, when in addition to

20:35.500 --> 20:37.500
payment for a certain amount

20:37.500 --> 20:39.500
of hours worked, the employee

20:39.500 --> 20:41.500
receives a bonus for quality,

20:41.500 --> 20:43.500
which can be reduced if

20:43.500 --> 20:45.500
this quality does not meet

20:45.500 --> 20:47.500
our requirements, or if

20:47.500 --> 20:49.500
the employee commits some

20:49.500 --> 20:51.500
violations of the discipline.

20:51.500 --> 20:53.500
Let's talk a little bit about

20:53.500 --> 20:55.500
collective or brigand forms

20:55.500 --> 20:57.500
of labor payment.

20:57.500 --> 20:59.500
We have already said that

20:59.500 --> 21:01.500
the accordant and accordant-premium

21:01.500 --> 21:03.500
systems are collective,

21:03.500 --> 21:05.500
because quite rarely one person

21:05.500 --> 21:07.500
can do a large amount of work.

21:07.500 --> 21:09.500
As a rule, it is a collective work.

21:09.500 --> 21:11.500
In terms of collective forms

21:11.500 --> 21:13.500
of labor payment, I want to

21:13.500 --> 21:15.500
touch on two points.

21:15.500 --> 21:17.500
As we said, we have employees

21:17.500 --> 21:19.500
who must give us the result,

21:19.500 --> 21:21.500
and we pay for the result.

21:21.500 --> 21:23.500
There are employees who must

21:23.500 --> 21:25.500
perform their functions, and we

21:25.500 --> 21:27.500
pay for their performance at a certain time.

21:27.500 --> 21:29.500
And there are employees whose mission

21:29.500 --> 21:31.500
is to organize the work of others.

21:31.500 --> 21:33.500
These are managers, these are managers.

21:33.500 --> 21:35.500
So we have to pay them for what?

21:35.500 --> 21:37.500
That's right, we have already

21:37.500 --> 21:39.500
mentioned this, for the collective result.

21:39.500 --> 21:41.500
How is labor payment distributed

21:41.500 --> 21:43.500
within the collective?

21:43.500 --> 21:45.500
We have agreed

21:45.500 --> 21:47.500
that for a certain

21:47.500 --> 21:49.500
time, let's say a month,

21:49.500 --> 21:51.500
we will implement a project

21:51.500 --> 21:53.500
for our employer.

21:53.500 --> 21:55.500
Let it be a consulting project

21:55.500 --> 21:57.500
for the implementation

21:57.500 --> 21:59.500
of our employer's

21:59.500 --> 22:01.500
effective labor payment system.

22:01.500 --> 22:03.500
Agreed? Great.

22:03.500 --> 22:05.500
And we have completed this work,

22:05.500 --> 22:07.500
and who of us should receive

22:07.500 --> 22:09.500
how much for it?

22:09.500 --> 22:11.500
There is a thing called

22:11.500 --> 22:13.500
the labor participation coefficient.

22:13.500 --> 22:15.500
This is a coefficient

22:15.500 --> 22:17.500
that is assigned to each

22:17.500 --> 22:19.500
of the members of our

22:19.500 --> 22:21.500
respected labor collective

22:21.500 --> 22:23.500
at the very beginning

22:23.500 --> 22:25.500
of the work or at the end of the work,

22:25.500 --> 22:27.500
and the rate of this worker

22:27.500 --> 22:29.500
increases or decreases

22:29.500 --> 22:31.500
according to how much he did,

22:31.500 --> 22:33.500
how much he invested,

22:33.500 --> 22:35.500
how much he worked there,

22:35.500 --> 22:37.500
what was his role,

22:37.500 --> 22:39.500
what was his mission.

22:39.500 --> 22:41.500
The labor participation coefficient

22:41.500 --> 22:43.500
can be assigned in a very different way.

22:43.500 --> 22:45.500
In some cases, it is initially

22:45.500 --> 22:47.500
negotiated in the contracts

22:47.500 --> 22:49.500
with the members of our collective,

22:49.500 --> 22:51.500
in other cases, as I said,

22:51.500 --> 22:53.500
by the total result, we estimate

22:53.500 --> 22:55.500
the final labor participation coefficient.

22:55.500 --> 22:57.500
There are very democratic situations

22:57.500 --> 22:59.500
when this labor participation coefficient

22:59.500 --> 23:01.500
is roughly assigned by the collective.

23:01.500 --> 23:03.500
There are absolutely dictatorial situations

23:03.500 --> 23:05.500
when this labor participation coefficient

23:05.500 --> 23:07.500
is assigned by the leader.

23:07.500 --> 23:09.500
Each time it is done in a different way

23:09.500 --> 23:11.500
depending on which form is more effective.

23:11.500 --> 23:13.500
These are the traditional

23:13.500 --> 23:15.500
compensation plans.

23:15.500 --> 23:17.500
Of course, you have heard these words.

23:17.500 --> 23:19.500
There is nothing new here.

23:19.500 --> 23:21.500
And at the same time,

23:21.500 --> 23:23.500
these plans can be used

23:23.500 --> 23:25.500
for the assessment

23:25.500 --> 23:27.500
and payment of labor

23:27.500 --> 23:29.500
in quite simple cases

23:29.500 --> 23:31.500
to very complex ones,

23:31.500 --> 23:33.500
such as the formation

23:33.500 --> 23:35.500
of the payment system

23:35.500 --> 23:37.500
of the same project workers.

23:37.500 --> 23:39.500
Therefore, I highly recommend

23:39.500 --> 23:41.500
not to forget about these simple

23:41.500 --> 23:43.500
compensation plans.

23:43.500 --> 23:45.500
There are many situations

23:45.500 --> 23:47.500
when the use of these traditional

23:47.500 --> 23:49.500
and understandable systems

23:49.500 --> 23:51.500
is not very effective.

23:51.500 --> 23:53.500
In general, you should not invent

23:53.500 --> 23:55.500
anything else.

23:55.500 --> 23:57.500
In other cases,

23:57.500 --> 23:59.500
it happens that you should.

23:59.500 --> 24:01.500
We will talk about

24:01.500 --> 24:03.500
how this will happen.

24:03.500 --> 24:05.500
One of the factors

24:05.500 --> 24:07.500
that ensure the attractiveness

24:07.500 --> 24:09.500
of the employer in the labor market

24:09.500 --> 24:11.500
is the assurance of the worker

24:11.500 --> 24:13.500
in the future

24:13.500 --> 24:15.500
and a certain level of stability.

24:15.500 --> 24:17.500
Although in most cases

24:17.500 --> 24:19.500
the payment of labor is somehow

24:19.500 --> 24:21.500
tied to its results,

24:21.500 --> 24:23.500
now almost everywhere,

24:23.500 --> 24:25.500
with a rare exception,

24:25.500 --> 24:27.500
combined forms of labor payment

24:27.500 --> 24:29.500
are used, which combine

24:29.500 --> 24:31.500
temporary payment

24:31.500 --> 24:33.500
with payment based on results.

24:33.500 --> 24:35.500
Therefore, it is especially important

24:35.500 --> 24:37.500
for us to understand how this

24:37.500 --> 24:39.500
constant component of labor payment

24:39.500 --> 24:41.500
is formed, according to which

24:41.500 --> 24:43.500
hourly payment is determined.

24:43.500 --> 24:45.500
Here we will have to remember

24:45.500 --> 24:47.500
that the term

24:47.500 --> 24:49.500
tariff grid

24:49.500 --> 24:51.500
is a word

24:51.500 --> 24:53.500
that is often used

24:53.500 --> 24:55.500
in English.

24:55.500 --> 24:57.500
In English,

24:57.500 --> 24:59.500
the word grid

24:59.500 --> 25:01.500
has several meanings,

25:01.500 --> 25:03.500
including the category,

25:03.500 --> 25:05.500
in this case the tariff.

25:05.500 --> 25:07.500
I prefer the Russian language

25:07.500 --> 25:09.500
and in the future

25:09.500 --> 25:11.500
I will use the word

25:11.500 --> 25:13.500
tariff grid to denote this concept.

25:13.500 --> 25:15.500
We divide all the employees

25:15.500 --> 25:17.500
of our enterprise,

25:17.500 --> 25:19.500
all the positions of our enterprise

25:19.500 --> 25:21.500
into a number of tariff categories

25:21.500 --> 25:23.500
and within each category

25:23.500 --> 25:25.500
we pay the employee

25:25.500 --> 25:27.500
in time as much as is provided

25:27.500 --> 25:29.500
in this category.

25:29.500 --> 25:31.500
Then we multiply by the number

25:31.500 --> 25:33.500
of working hours.

25:33.500 --> 25:35.500
What is the advantage of this scheme?

25:35.500 --> 25:37.500
First, it ensures a certain

25:37.500 --> 25:39.500
objectivity of labor assessment,

25:39.500 --> 25:41.500
because these categories of the tariff grid

25:41.500 --> 25:43.500
are not assigned from the top,

25:43.500 --> 25:45.500
but are specially developed

25:45.500 --> 25:47.500
to apply to the level

25:47.500 --> 25:49.500
of complexity of the work,

25:49.500 --> 25:51.500
what it requires from the employee

25:51.500 --> 25:53.500
and how valuable this work

25:53.500 --> 25:55.500
is for the enterprise.

25:55.500 --> 25:57.500
The second point,

25:57.500 --> 25:59.500
if we remember the factors

25:59.500 --> 26:01.500
of ensuring the efficiency of labor payment,

26:01.500 --> 26:03.500
is transparency, controllability

26:03.500 --> 26:05.500
and, what is very important,

26:05.500 --> 26:07.500
clarity for the employees.

26:07.500 --> 26:09.500
The employee understands

26:09.500 --> 26:11.500
what the tariff grid is,

26:11.500 --> 26:13.500
what the tariff category is,

26:13.500 --> 26:15.500
and what the conditions are.

26:17.500 --> 26:19.500
When the tariff grid is built

26:19.500 --> 26:21.500
and we know

26:21.500 --> 26:23.500
how many employees

26:23.500 --> 26:25.500
will receive

26:25.500 --> 26:27.500
and how much will be paid

26:27.500 --> 26:29.500
in advance,

26:29.500 --> 26:31.500
it is very easy to combine

26:31.500 --> 26:33.500
with the analysis of the enterprise economy

26:33.500 --> 26:35.500
and we can always understand

26:35.500 --> 26:37.500
how much of our labor payment

26:37.500 --> 26:39.500
is paid by the employees

26:39.500 --> 26:41.500
and we can understand

26:41.500 --> 26:43.500
how effective it is.

26:43.500 --> 26:45.500
As I said,

26:45.500 --> 26:47.500
this system is not only transparent

26:47.500 --> 26:49.500
for management,

26:49.500 --> 26:51.500
it is clear for the employees

26:51.500 --> 26:53.500
and provides them with a certain motivation

26:53.500 --> 26:55.500
and creates a clear perspective

26:55.500 --> 26:57.500
of career growth,

26:57.500 --> 26:59.500
in any case, much better

26:59.500 --> 27:01.500
than the traditional situation,

27:01.500 --> 27:03.500
when employees receive their salary

27:03.500 --> 27:05.500
in envelopes and no one knows

27:05.500 --> 27:07.500
or suspects anything.

27:09.500 --> 27:11.500
It seems that this system

27:11.500 --> 27:13.500
is quite rigid,

27:13.500 --> 27:15.500
but it is not so.

27:15.500 --> 27:17.500
It is flexible and adaptive

27:17.500 --> 27:19.500
because the entire system of grids

27:19.500 --> 27:21.500
can be moved up or down,

27:21.500 --> 27:23.500
it changes and it is clear

27:23.500 --> 27:25.500
how to change it.

27:25.500 --> 27:27.500
Therefore, it provides

27:27.500 --> 27:29.500
a high level of adaptability

27:29.500 --> 27:31.500
and adaptability

27:31.500 --> 27:33.500
to the conditions of the labor market.

27:33.500 --> 27:35.500
Today we can have

27:35.500 --> 27:37.500
one system, one tariff grid,

27:37.500 --> 27:39.500
and tomorrow we can change it

27:39.500 --> 27:41.500
according to what is happening

27:41.500 --> 27:43.500
in the labor market.

27:43.500 --> 27:45.500
I will say more,

27:45.500 --> 27:47.500
many enterprises move the tariff grid

27:47.500 --> 27:49.500
as a compensation for inflation.

27:49.500 --> 27:51.500
Tariff grid is revised

27:51.500 --> 27:53.500
every six months or every year

27:53.500 --> 27:55.500
taking into account inflation.

27:55.500 --> 27:57.500
Such advantages

27:57.500 --> 27:59.500
exist in this system.

27:59.500 --> 28:01.500
I will say right away

28:01.500 --> 28:03.500
that the implementation of the tariff grid

28:03.500 --> 28:05.500
where it was not is a big job.

28:05.500 --> 28:07.500
We will learn how to do it

28:07.500 --> 28:09.500
in the third part of our course.

28:09.500 --> 28:11.500
Now let's take a closer look

28:11.500 --> 28:13.500
at what it is.

28:13.500 --> 28:15.500
Here is the grid.

28:15.500 --> 28:17.500
Please look at the graph

28:17.500 --> 28:19.500
of the tariff grid

28:19.500 --> 28:21.500
shown on the next slide.

28:23.500 --> 28:25.500
We have several parameters

28:25.500 --> 28:27.500
that are important

28:27.500 --> 28:29.500
to determine

28:29.500 --> 28:31.500
the design of the tariff grid.

28:31.500 --> 28:33.500
The first one

28:33.500 --> 28:35.500
is the number of tariff categories.

28:35.500 --> 28:37.500
How many should there be?

28:37.500 --> 28:39.500
There are six of them in this picture.

28:39.500 --> 28:41.500
Maybe eight,

28:41.500 --> 28:43.500
maybe 16,

28:43.500 --> 28:45.500
but more than a few dozen

28:45.500 --> 28:47.500
are rarely seen here.

28:47.500 --> 28:49.500
The number of tariff categories

28:49.500 --> 28:51.500
depends on the perspective

28:51.500 --> 28:53.500
we want to create for our workers,

28:53.500 --> 28:55.500
how high the ladder

28:55.500 --> 28:57.500
they can climb

28:57.500 --> 28:59.500
and how many positions

28:59.500 --> 29:01.500
they can get.

29:01.500 --> 29:03.500
If the organization is large

29:03.500 --> 29:05.500
and there are many different people

29:05.500 --> 29:07.500
in different positions,

29:07.500 --> 29:09.500
then the tariff grid

29:09.500 --> 29:11.500
will probably have

29:11.500 --> 29:13.500
more categories.

29:13.500 --> 29:15.500
If it is not so,

29:15.500 --> 29:17.500
if the number of workers

29:17.500 --> 29:19.500
is small

29:19.500 --> 29:21.500
and the number of functions

29:21.500 --> 29:23.500
and positions is limited,

29:23.500 --> 29:25.500
then the tariff grid

29:25.500 --> 29:27.500
will probably be useless.

29:29.500 --> 29:31.500
The second question

29:31.500 --> 29:33.500
is about the variables

29:33.500 --> 29:35.500
such as the minimum wage

29:35.500 --> 29:37.500
and the maximum wage.

29:37.500 --> 29:39.500
The minimum wage

29:39.500 --> 29:41.500
corresponds to the lowest

29:41.500 --> 29:43.500
category of the tariff grid,

29:43.500 --> 29:45.500
and the maximum

29:45.500 --> 29:47.500
corresponds to the highest

29:47.500 --> 29:49.500
category of the tariff grid.

29:51.500 --> 29:53.500
What else is important to us?

29:53.500 --> 29:55.500
The width of the tariff category.

29:57.500 --> 29:59.500
How much does it fit?

30:01.500 --> 30:03.500
How wide is this range?

30:03.500 --> 30:05.500
Where does the tariff category

30:05.500 --> 30:07.500
end and where does it begin?

30:07.500 --> 30:09.500
It would seem easy to calculate

30:09.500 --> 30:11.500
if we know the minimum wage

30:11.500 --> 30:13.500
and the maximum wage.

30:13.500 --> 30:15.500
We simply subtract the minimum

30:15.500 --> 30:17.500
from the maximum,

30:17.500 --> 30:19.500
divide by the number of grades

30:19.500 --> 30:21.500
and get the width.

30:21.500 --> 30:23.500
The width of the tariff category

30:23.500 --> 30:25.500
shows a noticeable difference

30:25.500 --> 30:27.500
in the increase in the wage.

30:27.500 --> 30:29.500
This means that the tariff categories

30:29.500 --> 30:31.500
do not necessarily have

30:31.500 --> 30:33.500
the same width.

30:33.500 --> 30:35.500
In most cases,

30:35.500 --> 30:37.500
the low tariff categories

30:37.500 --> 30:39.500
will be smaller than the high

30:39.500 --> 30:41.500
tariff categories,

30:41.500 --> 30:43.500
simply because for workers

30:43.500 --> 30:45.500
at high wages

30:45.500 --> 30:47.500
the percentage ratio requires

30:47.500 --> 30:49.500
a greater increase

30:49.500 --> 30:51.500
in the wage.

30:51.500 --> 30:53.500
This is a very important point,

30:53.500 --> 30:55.500
because in some cases

30:55.500 --> 30:57.500
the tariff categories

30:57.500 --> 30:59.500
do not intersect,

30:59.500 --> 31:01.500
which means that

31:01.500 --> 31:03.500
the higher the tariff category

31:03.500 --> 31:05.500
begins where the lower

31:05.500 --> 31:07.500
ends.

31:07.500 --> 31:09.500
The jump from one category to another

31:09.500 --> 31:11.500
automatically means an increase

31:11.500 --> 31:13.500
in the wage.

31:13.500 --> 31:15.500
If the tariff categories intersect,

31:15.500 --> 31:17.500
it means that a person

31:17.500 --> 31:19.500
in the lower category

31:19.500 --> 31:21.500
can earn even more

31:21.500 --> 31:23.500
than a person in the higher category.

31:23.500 --> 31:25.500
Why do these intersections occur?

31:25.500 --> 31:27.500
These intersections are a very

31:27.500 --> 31:29.500
delicate management tool

31:29.500 --> 31:31.500
that provides us

31:31.500 --> 31:33.500
with a moral factor.

31:33.500 --> 31:35.500
In some cases,

31:35.500 --> 31:37.500
it turns out that

31:37.500 --> 31:39.500
the workers who have been

31:39.500 --> 31:41.500
working for us for a long time

31:41.500 --> 31:43.500
and who are attached to us

31:43.500 --> 31:45.500
are not able to

31:45.500 --> 31:47.500
work for us anymore.

31:47.500 --> 31:49.500
They earn a certain level,

31:49.500 --> 31:51.500
but this level

31:51.500 --> 31:53.500
does not correspond to the level

31:53.500 --> 31:55.500
that new workers require.

31:55.500 --> 31:57.500
We have to hire new workers

31:57.500 --> 31:59.500
at a higher wage

31:59.500 --> 32:01.500
than the old ones.

32:01.500 --> 32:03.500
Of course, this is unfair

32:03.500 --> 32:05.500
on the one hand,

32:05.500 --> 32:07.500
but on the other hand,

32:07.500 --> 32:09.500
it is simply unfair.

32:09.500 --> 32:11.500
And where do you go from the third side?

32:11.500 --> 32:13.500
The labor market is changing.

32:13.500 --> 32:15.500
The labor market allows us

32:15.500 --> 32:17.500
to manipulate the wage levels

32:17.500 --> 32:19.500
so that the worker,

32:19.500 --> 32:21.500
being at the fifth level,

32:21.500 --> 32:23.500
earns more than at the sixth.

32:23.500 --> 32:25.500
Thus, the necessary degree

32:25.500 --> 32:27.500
of justice is observed.

32:27.500 --> 32:29.500
This situation motivates

32:29.500 --> 32:31.500
workers more

32:31.500 --> 32:33.500
and does not encourage them

32:33.500 --> 32:35.500
to take offense

32:35.500 --> 32:37.500
and leave our enterprise.

32:37.500 --> 32:39.500
As we can see,

32:39.500 --> 32:41.500
it would seem that

32:41.500 --> 32:43.500
the labor market is changing,

32:43.500 --> 32:45.500
but on the other hand,

32:45.500 --> 32:47.500
there are many variables.

32:47.500 --> 32:49.500
When constructing a tariff grid,

32:49.500 --> 32:51.500
all these variables,

32:51.500 --> 32:53.500
both minimum and maximum wage,

32:53.500 --> 32:55.500
number of shifts, median,

32:55.500 --> 32:57.500
must be taken into account.

32:57.500 --> 32:59.500
The range for creativity

32:59.500 --> 33:01.500
is very wide.

33:01.500 --> 33:03.500
There is a point of view

33:03.500 --> 33:05.500
that the enterprise

33:05.500 --> 33:07.500
should be permeated

33:07.500 --> 33:09.500
by the tariff grid from bottom to top.

33:09.500 --> 33:11.500
The enterprise should take into account

33:11.500 --> 33:13.500
all the workers,

33:13.500 --> 33:15.500
where the lowest-class cleaner

33:15.500 --> 33:17.500
is at the bottom,

33:17.500 --> 33:19.500
and the director is at the top.

33:19.500 --> 33:21.500
I do not think this is right

33:21.500 --> 33:23.500
because a number of enterprises

33:23.500 --> 33:25.500
work as multifaceted enterprises.

33:25.500 --> 33:27.500
It is difficult to build

33:27.500 --> 33:29.500
a single tariff grid for the holding

33:29.500 --> 33:31.500
where several factories,

33:31.500 --> 33:33.500
logistics system,

33:33.500 --> 33:35.500
trading house,

33:35.500 --> 33:37.500
managing company,

33:37.500 --> 33:39.500
are all working together.

33:39.500 --> 33:41.500
Should it be built?

33:41.500 --> 33:43.500
I think it should not.

33:43.500 --> 33:45.500
It is necessary in cases

33:45.500 --> 33:47.500
when there are many workers,

33:47.500 --> 33:49.500
when the range of positions

33:49.500 --> 33:51.500
is wide enough,

33:51.500 --> 33:53.500
and it is necessary to sort it out

33:53.500 --> 33:55.500
and figure out who and how much

33:55.500 --> 33:57.500
we are going to pay.

33:57.500 --> 33:59.500
If the range is not so wide

33:59.500 --> 34:01.500
and the number of workers is not so large,

34:01.500 --> 34:03.500
we can limit ourselves

34:03.500 --> 34:05.500
to more primitive labor payment systems,

34:05.500 --> 34:07.500
without having to go through

34:07.500 --> 34:09.500
such a complex project

34:09.500 --> 34:11.500
as creating and introducing

34:11.500 --> 34:13.500
a tariff grid.

34:13.500 --> 34:15.500
Let's look at the next table.

34:15.500 --> 34:17.500
Here is a so-called

34:17.500 --> 34:19.500
matrix of grades

34:19.500 --> 34:21.500
for a tariff grid

34:21.500 --> 34:23.500
with 8 categories.

34:23.500 --> 34:25.500
Here is another

34:25.500 --> 34:27.500
big advantage of a tariff grid,

34:27.500 --> 34:29.500
namely the ability

34:29.500 --> 34:31.500
to compare the results of labor,

34:31.500 --> 34:33.500
the value of the enterprise

34:33.500 --> 34:35.500
and the level of labor payment

34:35.500 --> 34:37.500
of representatives

34:37.500 --> 34:39.500
of various departments

34:39.500 --> 34:41.500
who perform different work.

34:41.500 --> 34:43.500
As we can see from this grid,

34:43.500 --> 34:45.500
let's say, the fourth category.

34:45.500 --> 34:47.500
In the sales department

34:47.500 --> 34:49.500
we will have a manager

34:49.500 --> 34:51.500
of sales,

34:51.500 --> 34:53.500
in HR department

34:53.500 --> 34:55.500
a manager of selection of personnel,

34:55.500 --> 34:57.500
in the finance department

34:57.500 --> 34:59.500
an accountant.

34:59.500 --> 35:01.500
That is, there is an order

35:01.500 --> 35:03.500
and we can look at the organization

35:03.500 --> 35:05.500
as a whole,

35:05.500 --> 35:07.500
determine where we may have

35:07.500 --> 35:09.500
shortcomings.

35:09.500 --> 35:11.500
In those cases,

35:11.500 --> 35:13.500
when we observe sharp changes

35:13.500 --> 35:15.500
in the labor market of a structural nature,

35:15.500 --> 35:17.500
that is, not general,

35:17.500 --> 35:19.500
but in relation to individual specializations,

35:19.500 --> 35:21.500
education, profiles of specialists,

35:21.500 --> 35:23.500
and there is a deficit

35:23.500 --> 35:25.500
in the labor market,

35:25.500 --> 35:27.500
we can move the tariff grid

35:27.500 --> 35:29.500
in relation to those departments

35:29.500 --> 35:31.500
where such specialists work.

35:31.500 --> 35:33.500
Let's say,

35:33.500 --> 35:35.500
if there are necessary engineers

35:35.500 --> 35:37.500
at our enterprise,

35:37.500 --> 35:39.500
and the number of such engineers

35:39.500 --> 35:41.500
in the labor market is very limited,

35:41.500 --> 35:43.500
in this case we can move

35:43.500 --> 35:45.500
and change some of the grids

35:45.500 --> 35:47.500
so that our offer

35:47.500 --> 35:49.500
becomes more attractive for these workers.

35:49.500 --> 35:51.500
So, colleagues,

35:51.500 --> 35:53.500
we have finished with the summary

35:53.500 --> 35:55.500
of the permanent part of the labor payment

35:55.500 --> 35:57.500
and we will move on to the variable,

35:57.500 --> 35:59.500
that is, the premium part.

35:59.500 --> 36:01.500
In order to summarize the premium part,

36:01.500 --> 36:03.500
there are many ways,

36:03.500 --> 36:05.500
coefficients,

36:05.500 --> 36:07.500
regulations,

36:07.500 --> 36:09.500
and we will definitely address this

36:09.500 --> 36:11.500
in the third part of our course.

36:11.500 --> 36:13.500
But now I would like to talk

36:13.500 --> 36:15.500
a little about the now widespread

36:15.500 --> 36:17.500
and very good,

36:17.500 --> 36:19.500
effective,

36:19.500 --> 36:21.500
working, clear and transparent system,

36:21.500 --> 36:23.500
which is called

36:23.500 --> 36:25.500
the system of key indicators

36:25.500 --> 36:27.500
or in English

36:27.500 --> 36:29.500
the key productivity indicators.

36:29.500 --> 36:31.500
We discussed this system

36:31.500 --> 36:33.500
in our course on personal assessment,

36:33.500 --> 36:35.500
now we will return to it again.

36:35.500 --> 36:37.500
Let me remind you in a nutshell

36:37.500 --> 36:39.500
what we are talking about.

36:39.500 --> 36:41.500
We have our organization as a whole,

36:41.500 --> 36:43.500
a large organization,

36:43.500 --> 36:45.500
our corporation,

36:45.500 --> 36:47.500
which has strategic plans.

36:47.500 --> 36:49.500
In order to understand

36:49.500 --> 36:51.500
whether we have implemented

36:51.500 --> 36:53.500
these plans or not,

36:53.500 --> 36:55.500
we need a set of indicators,

36:55.500 --> 36:57.500
indicators that will be

36:57.500 --> 36:59.500
clear and accountable,

36:59.500 --> 37:01.500
and we can say whether we have implemented

37:01.500 --> 37:03.500
them or not.

37:03.500 --> 37:05.500
In order to implement the plans of the corporation

37:05.500 --> 37:07.500
as a whole,

37:07.500 --> 37:09.500
each unit must perform

37:09.500 --> 37:11.500
its functions.

37:11.500 --> 37:13.500
Based on the company's plans,

37:13.500 --> 37:15.500
plans of its departments are built,

37:15.500 --> 37:17.500
for which this system of key indicators

37:17.500 --> 37:19.500
is also created.

37:19.500 --> 37:21.500
So, from top to bottom,

37:21.500 --> 37:23.500
each employee receives

37:23.500 --> 37:25.500
his own key indicator,

37:25.500 --> 37:27.500
which he must rely on.

37:27.500 --> 37:29.500
The payment of bonuses

37:29.500 --> 37:31.500
depends on how

37:31.500 --> 37:33.500
these indicators are implemented.

37:33.500 --> 37:35.500
If 100%, then the employee

37:35.500 --> 37:37.500
will receive 100% of his bonus,

37:37.500 --> 37:39.500
if not, then most likely not.

37:39.500 --> 37:41.500
But if 150%, then maybe

37:41.500 --> 37:43.500
150% of his bonus.

37:43.500 --> 37:45.500
The advantage of this system is

37:45.500 --> 37:47.500
that each employee,

37:47.500 --> 37:49.500
each unit knows

37:49.500 --> 37:51.500
how much he will be rewarded,

37:51.500 --> 37:53.500
even if the unit is functional

37:53.500 --> 37:55.500
and does not work for the result,

37:55.500 --> 37:57.500
but for the process.

37:57.500 --> 37:59.500
It would seem that there should be

37:59.500 --> 38:01.500
only a temporary form of labor payment.

38:01.500 --> 38:03.500
This is not the case.

38:03.500 --> 38:05.500
For each unit, including the accounting,

38:05.500 --> 38:07.500
the office,

38:07.500 --> 38:09.500
and all other units

38:09.500 --> 38:11.500
that work on the process,

38:11.500 --> 38:13.500
you can enter 2, 3, 4, 5 indicators

38:13.500 --> 38:15.500
that will clearly determine

38:15.500 --> 38:17.500
how well they worked.

38:17.500 --> 38:19.500
The most primitive of them

38:19.500 --> 38:21.500
is the number of errors.

38:21.500 --> 38:23.500
Whether they were allowed or not.

38:23.500 --> 38:25.500
The most important thing here

38:25.500 --> 38:27.500
is that these indicators

38:27.500 --> 38:29.500
are clearly and unambiguously written.

38:29.500 --> 38:31.500
What is the disadvantage of this system?

38:31.500 --> 38:33.500
It is very difficult to implement.

38:33.500 --> 38:35.500
When a corporation is large,

38:35.500 --> 38:37.500
the implementation of such a system

38:37.500 --> 38:39.500
requires several years,

38:39.500 --> 38:41.500
huge costs,

38:41.500 --> 38:43.500
and is not always justified.

38:43.500 --> 38:45.500
But I want to say that

38:45.500 --> 38:47.500
if we do not create a system of KPIs

38:47.500 --> 38:49.500
for the organization as a whole,

38:49.500 --> 38:51.500
we can introduce such KPIs

38:51.500 --> 38:53.500
for individual units

38:53.500 --> 38:55.500
and for individual positions.

38:55.500 --> 38:57.500
The advantage is that the employee

38:57.500 --> 38:59.500
will understand what we will

38:59.500 --> 39:01.500
fund him for,

39:01.500 --> 39:03.500
and we will understand it very well.

39:03.500 --> 39:05.500
As for the employees whose tasks

39:05.500 --> 39:07.500
are functional,

39:07.500 --> 39:09.500
I want to give the following example,

39:09.500 --> 39:11.500
which is very indicative

39:11.500 --> 39:13.500
and historical.

39:13.500 --> 39:15.500
There is a legend

39:15.500 --> 39:17.500
that the great and wise king Solomon

39:17.500 --> 39:19.500
paid his regular doctor

39:19.500 --> 39:21.500
only when he was healthy.

39:21.500 --> 39:23.500
But when he was ill,

39:23.500 --> 39:25.500
he stopped paying.

39:25.500 --> 39:27.500
Guess what the doctor did

39:27.500 --> 39:29.500
and what he would do

39:29.500 --> 39:31.500
if he were paid exactly the opposite.

39:31.500 --> 39:33.500
In translation into our language,

39:33.500 --> 39:35.500
this means that for the doctor

39:35.500 --> 39:37.500
the key indicator of efficiency

39:37.500 --> 39:39.500
was the health of his employer.

39:39.500 --> 39:41.500
Accordingly, if the PPI was not carried out,

39:41.500 --> 39:43.500
the salary was not produced.

39:43.500 --> 39:45.500
We discussed in detail

39:45.500 --> 39:47.500
the system of formation

39:47.500 --> 39:49.500
of the permanent part

39:49.500 --> 39:51.500
of the salary

39:51.500 --> 39:53.500
and talked about the formation

39:53.500 --> 39:55.500
of the premium component.

39:55.500 --> 39:57.500
Now let's turn to the next component

39:57.500 --> 39:59.500
of the stimulation system,

39:59.500 --> 40:01.500
which is called the social package.

40:01.500 --> 40:03.500
There are many legends

40:03.500 --> 40:05.500
and many hypotheses

40:05.500 --> 40:07.500
that the system

40:07.500 --> 40:09.500
of payment

40:09.500 --> 40:11.500
is a system of payment.

40:11.500 --> 40:13.500
There are many social myths

40:13.500 --> 40:15.500
and many points of view.

40:15.500 --> 40:17.500
In particular,

40:17.500 --> 40:19.500
there is a point of view

40:19.500 --> 40:21.500
that if we pay a lot to people,

40:21.500 --> 40:23.500
why should we provide

40:23.500 --> 40:25.500
some social package?

40:25.500 --> 40:27.500
This point of view existed

40:27.500 --> 40:29.500
for a while,

40:29.500 --> 40:31.500
but then it disappeared.

40:31.500 --> 40:33.500
It turns out that not everything

40:33.500 --> 40:35.500
that an organization needs

40:35.500 --> 40:37.500
is in the state of people

40:37.500 --> 40:39.500
at the expense of their labor.

40:39.500 --> 40:41.500
Let's talk about the purpose

40:41.500 --> 40:43.500
of the social package.

40:43.500 --> 40:45.500
First, it is a positive

40:45.500 --> 40:47.500
image of the employer.

40:47.500 --> 40:49.500
Or, as we said,

40:49.500 --> 40:51.500
if the organization allows

40:51.500 --> 40:53.500
the creation of a social package,

40:53.500 --> 40:55.500
it means that it is stable,

40:55.500 --> 40:57.500
has certain reserves,

40:57.500 --> 40:59.500
intends to work further,

40:59.500 --> 41:01.500
and such an organization

41:01.500 --> 41:03.500
looks more reliable

41:03.500 --> 41:05.500
as an employer.

41:05.500 --> 41:07.500
Second,

41:07.500 --> 41:09.500
by providing the employees

41:09.500 --> 41:11.500
with a social package,

41:11.500 --> 41:13.500
we show respect to them,

41:13.500 --> 41:15.500
we show that they are

41:15.500 --> 41:17.500
important to us.

41:17.500 --> 41:19.500
When a person in an organization

41:19.500 --> 41:21.500
that has a social package

41:21.500 --> 41:23.500
comes home and shows

41:23.500 --> 41:25.500
his family

41:25.500 --> 41:27.500
what he gets from the organization

41:27.500 --> 41:29.500
except for the labor payment,

41:29.500 --> 41:31.500
it usually works on his prestige,

41:31.500 --> 41:33.500
raises his self-esteem,

41:33.500 --> 41:35.500
and it is a positive image.

41:35.500 --> 41:37.500
I want to give you a strange example.

41:37.500 --> 41:39.500
Now, in most cases,

41:39.500 --> 41:41.500
managers are hired

41:41.500 --> 41:43.500
and asked if the social package

41:43.500 --> 41:45.500
provides for the payment of mobile communication.

41:45.500 --> 41:47.500
It is quite strange.

41:47.500 --> 41:49.500
Can people with such a high

41:49.500 --> 41:51.500
labor payment

41:51.500 --> 41:53.500
not find money

41:53.500 --> 41:55.500
for a mobile phone payment?

41:55.500 --> 41:57.500
In fact, it is a purely moral factor.

41:57.500 --> 41:59.500
If we pay a person

41:59.500 --> 42:01.500
for mobile communication,

42:01.500 --> 42:03.500
we show that he is so important

42:03.500 --> 42:05.500
that he should be in touch

42:05.500 --> 42:07.500
and we are ready to pay for it.

42:07.500 --> 42:09.500
This is a demonstration

42:09.500 --> 42:11.500
of his importance.

42:11.500 --> 42:13.500
I think that if we paid

42:13.500 --> 42:15.500
for the payment of the canteen,

42:15.500 --> 42:17.500
instead of the high-paid worker,

42:17.500 --> 42:19.500
they would not be so happy.

42:19.500 --> 42:21.500
Or the payment of shirts.

42:21.500 --> 42:23.500
They would not be as happy

42:23.500 --> 42:25.500
as the payment of a mobile phone.

42:25.500 --> 42:27.500
The next point

42:27.500 --> 42:29.500
is the fact

42:29.500 --> 42:31.500
that it is just

42:31.500 --> 42:33.500
an increase in the ability

42:33.500 --> 42:35.500
of our employees.

42:35.500 --> 42:37.500
The well-known

42:37.500 --> 42:39.500
components of the social package

42:39.500 --> 42:41.500
are medical insurance,

42:41.500 --> 42:43.500
food,

42:43.500 --> 42:45.500
and payment of travel.

42:45.500 --> 42:47.500
In some cases,

42:47.500 --> 42:49.500
it is the delivery of employees

42:49.500 --> 42:51.500
from the nearest metro station

42:51.500 --> 42:53.500
to the office.

42:53.500 --> 42:55.500
We help people in this way,

42:55.500 --> 42:57.500
but we also solve one problem.

42:57.500 --> 42:59.500
If a person is sick,

42:59.500 --> 43:01.500
he needs to be treated.

43:01.500 --> 43:03.500
If he comes to work

43:03.500 --> 43:05.500
by public transport,

43:05.500 --> 43:07.500
he will be nervous,

43:07.500 --> 43:09.500
he will feel bad,

43:09.500 --> 43:11.500
he will be late for work.

43:11.500 --> 43:13.500
And if he comes back,

43:13.500 --> 43:15.500
he will complain about traffic jams.

43:15.500 --> 43:17.500
If a person gets to the office

43:17.500 --> 43:19.500
by car, he will complain

43:19.500 --> 43:21.500
about traffic jams.

43:21.500 --> 43:23.500
He will complain about it

43:23.500 --> 43:25.500
and he will be nervous.

43:25.500 --> 43:27.500
Therefore, we provide

43:27.500 --> 43:29.500
a higher level of

43:29.500 --> 43:31.500
employability for our employees.

43:33.500 --> 43:35.500
The last point is

43:35.500 --> 43:37.500
the solution of problems

43:37.500 --> 43:39.500
that interfere with the work of our employees.

43:39.500 --> 43:41.500
We could give money to our employees,

43:41.500 --> 43:43.500
but we will soon see an example

43:43.500 --> 43:45.500
that shows

43:45.500 --> 43:47.500
how much more effective

43:47.500 --> 43:49.500
it is to solve the problems

43:49.500 --> 43:51.500
of our employees

43:51.500 --> 43:53.500
than to pay them.

43:53.500 --> 43:55.500
In such cases,

43:55.500 --> 43:57.500
problems are not solved

43:57.500 --> 43:59.500
with money.

43:59.500 --> 44:01.500
In such cases,

44:01.500 --> 44:03.500
we should create a social package.

44:03.500 --> 44:05.500
We are kind and we want

44:05.500 --> 44:07.500
to do good to our employees.

44:07.500 --> 44:09.500
It is very pleasant.

44:09.500 --> 44:11.500
Unfortunately, we are a commercial organization

44:11.500 --> 44:13.500
and our task is to earn money.

44:13.500 --> 44:15.500
Therefore, it would be unprofitable

44:15.500 --> 44:17.500
to invest money in nothing.

44:17.500 --> 44:19.500
Therefore, when we create

44:19.500 --> 44:21.500
a social package for our organization,

44:21.500 --> 44:23.500
we should take into account

44:23.500 --> 44:25.500
the savings of expenses

44:25.500 --> 44:27.500
that we would have incurred

44:27.500 --> 44:29.500
if we did not have a social package.

44:29.500 --> 44:31.500
Secondly,

44:31.500 --> 44:33.500
very often organizations

44:33.500 --> 44:35.500
offer such goods and services

44:35.500 --> 44:37.500
as a part of the social package

44:37.500 --> 44:39.500
that the organization

44:39.500 --> 44:41.500
can solve better

44:41.500 --> 44:43.500
than the employee.

44:43.500 --> 44:45.500
I will give you an example.

44:45.500 --> 44:47.500
The organization offers

44:47.500 --> 44:49.500
a bank guarantee

44:49.500 --> 44:51.500
for the payment of loans.

44:51.500 --> 44:53.500
The organization cannot provide

44:53.500 --> 44:55.500
such guarantees for itself.

44:55.500 --> 44:57.500
Or, let's say,

44:57.500 --> 44:59.500
we sign a collective insurance contract

44:59.500 --> 45:01.500
with an insurance company

45:01.500 --> 45:03.500
for the life and medical insurance

45:03.500 --> 45:05.500
of our employees.

45:05.500 --> 45:07.500
We would have done it

45:07.500 --> 45:09.500
if each of our employees

45:09.500 --> 45:11.500
signed such a contract.

45:11.500 --> 45:13.500
This would have cost

45:13.500 --> 45:15.500
much more money.

45:15.500 --> 45:17.500
We would have bought

45:17.500 --> 45:19.500
a social insurance service

45:19.500 --> 45:21.500
for our employees.

45:21.500 --> 45:23.500
What else can we do?

45:23.500 --> 45:25.500
The fact is that

45:25.500 --> 45:27.500
the so-called

45:27.500 --> 45:29.500
insurance culture of the population

45:29.500 --> 45:31.500
is not well developed in our country.

45:31.500 --> 45:33.500
Our people do not like

45:33.500 --> 45:35.500
to be insured,

45:35.500 --> 45:37.500
unlike, for example,

45:37.500 --> 45:39.500
Americans or Europeans

45:39.500 --> 45:41.500
who know that they should be insured

45:41.500 --> 45:43.500
because there are risks.

45:43.500 --> 45:45.500
If our organization

45:45.500 --> 45:47.500
had a social insurance system

45:47.500 --> 45:49.500
with a family budget,

45:49.500 --> 45:51.500
our employees would have forgotten

45:51.500 --> 45:53.500
about it.

45:53.500 --> 45:55.500
Our employees are insured.

45:55.500 --> 45:57.500
They are happy and we are satisfied.

45:57.500 --> 45:59.500
So, once again,

45:59.500 --> 46:01.500
there are two important factors.

46:01.500 --> 46:03.500
First, the cost savings.

46:03.500 --> 46:05.500
Second, the efficiency of our staff.

46:05.500 --> 46:07.500
Third, the ability of our organization

46:07.500 --> 46:09.500
to solve problems better

