59:33.500 --> 59:35.500
on our corporate personnel policy,

59:35.500 --> 59:37.500
on the market sector in which we work,

59:37.500 --> 59:39.500
and so on.

59:39.500 --> 59:41.500
The first thing we need to do

59:41.500 --> 59:43.500
in order to distribute positions

59:43.500 --> 59:45.500
in our company

59:45.500 --> 59:47.500
on a certain grid,

59:47.500 --> 59:49.500
we need to make a description

59:49.500 --> 59:51.500
and an assessment of these positions.

59:51.500 --> 59:53.500
What is included here?

59:53.500 --> 59:55.500
For each position,

59:55.500 --> 59:57.500
we must specify the following parameters.

59:57.500 --> 59:59.500
The first is the name of the position,

59:59.500 --> 01:00:01.500
so that we can identify it.

01:00:03.500 --> 01:00:05.500
The second is its purpose.

01:00:05.500 --> 01:00:07.500
Why is it needed in the organization?

01:00:07.500 --> 01:00:09.500
What does a person do

01:00:09.500 --> 01:00:11.500
in this position?

01:00:11.500 --> 01:00:13.500
I must tell you right away

01:00:13.500 --> 01:00:15.500
that the assessment sometimes shows

01:00:15.500 --> 01:00:17.500
that some positions are absolutely unnecessary,

01:00:17.500 --> 01:00:19.500
and in vain they exist.

01:00:19.500 --> 01:00:21.500
The third is the place

01:00:21.500 --> 01:00:23.500
in the organizational structure

01:00:23.500 --> 01:00:25.500
of this position,

01:00:25.500 --> 01:00:27.500
to whom it is subordinate,

01:00:27.500 --> 01:00:29.500
and what role it plays in the organizational diagram.

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:31.500
This is a very important and useful process of analysis,

01:00:31.500 --> 01:00:33.500
because it may turn out

01:00:33.500 --> 01:00:35.500
that our position is suspended somewhere

01:00:35.500 --> 01:00:37.500
and it is not very clear

01:00:37.500 --> 01:00:39.500
to whom the employee who is on it is subordinate.

01:00:39.500 --> 01:00:41.500
Or maybe it is in the wrong place

01:00:41.500 --> 01:00:43.500
and it will have to be moved

01:00:43.500 --> 01:00:45.500
to improve the efficiency of our enterprise.

01:00:45.500 --> 01:00:47.500
The next thing is

01:00:47.500 --> 01:00:49.500
who and what positions

01:00:49.500 --> 01:00:51.500
are subordinate

01:00:51.500 --> 01:00:53.500
to the positions we are considering.

01:00:53.500 --> 01:00:55.500
I mean direct subordination,

01:00:55.500 --> 01:00:57.500
which is conditioned

01:00:57.500 --> 01:00:59.500
by the organizational structure,

01:00:59.500 --> 01:01:01.500
and functional subordination,

01:01:01.500 --> 01:01:03.500
that is, indirect subordination.

01:01:03.500 --> 01:01:05.500
When an employee in this position

01:01:05.500 --> 01:01:07.500
has the right to manage

01:01:07.500 --> 01:01:09.500
in one way or another

01:01:09.500 --> 01:01:11.500
other people at our enterprise

01:01:11.500 --> 01:01:13.500
who are not subordinate to him.

01:01:13.500 --> 01:01:15.500
For example,

01:01:15.500 --> 01:01:17.500
a sales department employee

01:01:17.500 --> 01:01:19.500
can manage a warehouse worker

01:01:19.500 --> 01:01:21.500
who releases the purchased

01:01:21.500 --> 01:01:23.500
product to the buyer.

01:01:23.500 --> 01:01:25.500
The next thing

01:01:25.500 --> 01:01:27.500
that is extremely important

01:01:27.500 --> 01:01:29.500
is the determination of key functions

01:01:29.500 --> 01:01:31.500
and responsibilities.

01:01:31.500 --> 01:01:33.500
That is, in fact, the duty instruction

01:01:33.500 --> 01:01:35.500
what this person should do at work.

01:01:35.500 --> 01:01:37.500
And there should not be many of these functions.

01:01:37.500 --> 01:01:39.500
They should be clear,

01:01:39.500 --> 01:01:41.500
but at the same time they should be very clear.

01:01:41.500 --> 01:01:43.500
In some cases,

01:01:43.500 --> 01:01:45.500
it turns out that functions

01:01:45.500 --> 01:01:47.500
that no one performs at the enterprise

01:01:47.500 --> 01:01:49.500
are formed,

01:01:49.500 --> 01:01:51.500
they should be performed.

01:01:51.500 --> 01:01:53.500
And this duplication should also be avoided.

01:01:53.500 --> 01:01:55.500
The next thing is the education

01:01:55.500 --> 01:01:57.500
that is required

01:01:57.500 --> 01:01:59.500
to take this position.

01:01:59.500 --> 01:02:01.500
Sometimes this education

01:02:01.500 --> 01:02:03.500
is very high.

01:02:03.500 --> 01:02:05.500
Sometimes we overestimate them.

01:02:05.500 --> 01:02:07.500
There are a number of cases

01:02:07.500 --> 01:02:09.500
when a person without a higher education

01:02:09.500 --> 01:02:11.500
can quite well cope

01:02:11.500 --> 01:02:13.500
with this position,

01:02:13.500 --> 01:02:15.500
and we require that he

01:02:15.500 --> 01:02:17.500
must have completed the higher education.

01:02:17.500 --> 01:02:19.500
And what is very important

01:02:19.500 --> 01:02:21.500
is the improvement of the qualification.

01:02:21.500 --> 01:02:23.500
As I said,

01:02:23.500 --> 01:02:25.500
we live in a world of constant changes,

01:02:25.500 --> 01:02:27.500
and it is impossible to stand still.

01:02:27.500 --> 01:02:29.500
And for a number of positions

01:02:29.500 --> 01:02:31.500
a person must,

01:02:31.500 --> 01:02:33.500
a person needs to

01:02:33.500 --> 01:02:35.500
effectively fulfill his duties,

01:02:35.500 --> 01:02:37.500
but quite often

01:02:37.500 --> 01:02:39.500
to pass a certain improvement of the qualification.

01:02:39.500 --> 01:02:41.500
This is especially true of our accountants,

01:02:41.500 --> 01:02:43.500
because, as we know,

01:02:43.500 --> 01:02:45.500
our tax legislation and the law

01:02:45.500 --> 01:02:47.500
tend to change periodically.

01:02:47.500 --> 01:02:49.500
The required work experience.

01:02:49.500 --> 01:02:51.500
What work experience

01:02:51.500 --> 01:02:53.500
does a person need

01:02:53.500 --> 01:02:55.500
to take this position?

01:02:55.500 --> 01:02:57.500
Accordingly, if it is a large one,

01:02:57.500 --> 01:02:59.500
then the position will weigh more.

01:02:59.500 --> 01:03:01.500
If it is insignificant,

01:03:01.500 --> 01:03:03.500
then it will weigh less.

01:03:03.500 --> 01:03:05.500
Description of knowledge, skills, competencies,

01:03:05.500 --> 01:03:07.500
paying attention to special

01:03:07.500 --> 01:03:09.500
special skills and knowledge

01:03:09.500 --> 01:03:11.500
that are necessary

01:03:11.500 --> 01:03:13.500
for this position,

01:03:13.500 --> 01:03:15.500
and not at all.

01:03:15.500 --> 01:03:17.500
Another very important point

01:03:17.500 --> 01:03:19.500
is the question of responsibility.

01:03:19.500 --> 01:03:21.500
What does responsibility mean?

01:03:21.500 --> 01:03:23.500
What results

01:03:23.500 --> 01:03:25.500
can our organization have

01:03:25.500 --> 01:03:27.500
when an employee

01:03:27.500 --> 01:03:29.500
takes the wrong decision

01:03:29.500 --> 01:03:31.500
or behaves wrongly?

01:03:31.500 --> 01:03:33.500
What results does this person

01:03:33.500 --> 01:03:35.500
answer for?

01:03:35.500 --> 01:03:37.500
These results can be organizational

01:03:37.500 --> 01:03:39.500
or financial.

01:03:39.500 --> 01:03:41.500
In a number of cases

01:03:41.500 --> 01:03:43.500
for different levels of positions

01:03:43.500 --> 01:03:45.500
the amount of financial resources

01:03:45.500 --> 01:03:47.500
that a person can allocate

01:03:47.500 --> 01:03:49.500
without asking anyone

01:03:49.500 --> 01:03:51.500
is determined.

01:03:51.500 --> 01:03:53.500
And above this amount

01:03:53.500 --> 01:03:55.500
the person must turn to the higher management.

01:03:55.500 --> 01:03:57.500
To determine the premium part,

01:03:57.500 --> 01:03:59.500
we need to do a boil,

01:03:59.500 --> 01:04:01.500
as we have already said.

01:04:01.500 --> 01:04:03.500
That is, 3-5 indicators

01:04:03.500 --> 01:04:05.500
that are key for this position

01:04:05.500 --> 01:04:07.500
so that we can say

01:04:07.500 --> 01:04:09.500
whether a person works effectively

01:04:09.500 --> 01:04:11.500
or not, or not at all.

01:04:11.500 --> 01:04:13.500
Agree that the procedure

01:04:13.500 --> 01:04:15.500
is not easy, it takes a lot of time.

01:04:15.500 --> 01:04:17.500
The main question is where

01:04:17.500 --> 01:04:19.500
we will get this information.

01:04:19.500 --> 01:04:21.500
Most often this information is collected

01:04:21.500 --> 01:04:23.500
by the organization using special procedures

01:04:23.500 --> 01:04:25.500
where the analysis of documents,

01:04:25.500 --> 01:04:27.500
monitoring of people at work,

01:04:27.500 --> 01:04:29.500
as well as surveys are included.

01:04:29.500 --> 01:04:31.500
Special survey sheets are created.

01:04:31.500 --> 01:04:33.500
There are already standardized sheets.

01:04:33.500 --> 01:04:35.500
In some cases,

01:04:35.500 --> 01:04:37.500
they will have to be created by ourselves.

01:04:37.500 --> 01:04:39.500
Nevertheless,

01:04:39.500 --> 01:04:41.500
we collect the information

01:04:41.500 --> 01:04:43.500
in a certain way and approve it

01:04:43.500 --> 01:04:45.500
to the management.

01:04:45.500 --> 01:04:47.500
According to the description of positions,

01:04:47.500 --> 01:04:49.500
we can weigh the positions,

01:04:49.500 --> 01:04:51.500
that is, compare them

01:04:51.500 --> 01:04:53.500
and distribute them along the grid

01:04:53.500 --> 01:04:55.500
that we have already mentioned

01:04:55.500 --> 01:04:57.500
and which is our goal

01:04:57.500 --> 01:04:59.500
in the implementation of this difficult work.

01:04:59.500 --> 01:05:01.500
How can we evaluate positions

01:05:01.500 --> 01:05:03.500
after we have described them?

01:05:03.500 --> 01:05:05.500
There are only three methods.

01:05:05.500 --> 01:05:07.500
Classification,

01:05:07.500 --> 01:05:09.500
Arranging

01:05:09.500 --> 01:05:11.500
and Binary Factor Method.

01:05:11.500 --> 01:05:13.500
Classification is when

01:05:13.500 --> 01:05:15.500
we set a certain grid in advance

01:05:15.500 --> 01:05:17.500
and lay out the positions

01:05:17.500 --> 01:05:19.500
along this grid

01:05:19.500 --> 01:05:21.500
according to the results

01:05:21.500 --> 01:05:23.500
described by me.

01:05:23.500 --> 01:05:25.500
Arranging is when we take all the positions

01:05:25.500 --> 01:05:27.500
in our organization

01:05:27.500 --> 01:05:29.500
and distribute them, for example,

01:05:29.500 --> 01:05:31.500
by the method of pair comparison.

01:05:31.500 --> 01:05:33.500
Which position is more difficult, A or B?

01:05:33.500 --> 01:05:35.500
Probably A.

01:05:35.500 --> 01:05:37.500
A, B or C?

01:05:37.500 --> 01:05:39.500
C.

01:05:39.500 --> 01:05:41.500
Thus, we arrange all the positions

01:05:41.500 --> 01:05:43.500
from the lowest

01:05:43.500 --> 01:05:45.500
in our system of grades

01:05:45.500 --> 01:05:47.500
to the highest.

01:05:47.500 --> 01:05:49.500
You will agree that classification

01:05:49.500 --> 01:05:51.500
and arranging seem to be quite simple methods,

01:05:51.500 --> 01:05:53.500
but this is not quite the case,

01:05:53.500 --> 01:05:55.500
because both

01:05:55.500 --> 01:05:57.500
carry a lot of information noise,

01:05:57.500 --> 01:05:59.500
contradictions in decision-making,

01:05:59.500 --> 01:06:01.500
as well as subjectivism.

01:06:01.500 --> 01:06:03.500
To avoid all this,

01:06:03.500 --> 01:06:05.500
the so-called binary factor method

01:06:05.500 --> 01:06:07.500
has been developed.

01:06:07.500 --> 01:06:09.500
There are several of them.

01:06:09.500 --> 01:06:11.500
We will consider

01:06:11.500 --> 01:06:13.500
this method

01:06:13.500 --> 01:06:15.500
using the example of one of them,

01:06:15.500 --> 01:06:17.500
which is the most common

01:06:17.500 --> 01:06:19.500
and well-known in the world.

01:06:19.500 --> 01:06:21.500
I mean the system

01:06:21.500 --> 01:06:23.500
proposed by the organization Hey! Group,

01:06:23.500 --> 01:06:25.500
which is also called

01:06:25.500 --> 01:06:27.500
Hey's method.

01:06:27.500 --> 01:06:29.500
So, binary factor method.

01:06:29.500 --> 01:06:31.500
What should be done for this?

01:06:31.500 --> 01:06:33.500
First, we select

01:06:33.500 --> 01:06:35.500
the factors

01:06:35.500 --> 01:06:37.500
that are important for the organization.

01:06:37.500 --> 01:06:39.500
Moreover, for each of these factors

01:06:39.500 --> 01:06:41.500
we must determine their weight,

01:06:41.500 --> 01:06:43.500
that is, how important

01:06:43.500 --> 01:06:45.500
this factor is for the organization,

01:06:45.500 --> 01:06:47.500
based on the total weight

01:06:47.500 --> 01:06:49.500
of the factors, 100%.

01:06:49.500 --> 01:06:51.500
We will see how this is done a little later.

01:06:51.500 --> 01:06:53.500
Secondly, we describe the positions

01:06:53.500 --> 01:06:55.500
based on the example

01:06:55.500 --> 01:06:57.500
that you have just seen in the slide,

01:06:57.500 --> 01:06:59.500
and we assess the weight

01:06:59.500 --> 01:07:01.500
of each factor in this position.

01:07:01.500 --> 01:07:03.500
On the one hand,

01:07:03.500 --> 01:07:05.500
the importance of the factor for the organization,

01:07:05.500 --> 01:07:07.500
and on the other hand,

01:07:07.500 --> 01:07:09.500
the presence of this factor

01:07:09.500 --> 01:07:11.500
at this workplace.

01:07:11.500 --> 01:07:13.500
What does this mean?

01:07:13.500 --> 01:07:15.500
For example, such a factor

01:07:15.500 --> 01:07:17.500
as making independent decisions.

01:07:17.500 --> 01:07:19.500
For the organization as a whole,

01:07:19.500 --> 01:07:21.500
this may be a very important factor,

01:07:21.500 --> 01:07:23.500
or maybe not, because decisions

01:07:23.500 --> 01:07:25.500
do not need to be made in particular.

01:07:25.500 --> 01:07:27.500
It is arranged in such a way

01:07:27.500 --> 01:07:29.500
that the manager of the company

01:07:29.500 --> 01:07:31.500
must make decisions

01:07:31.500 --> 01:07:33.500
for the company,

01:07:33.500 --> 01:07:35.500
because the market is changing,

01:07:35.500 --> 01:07:37.500
the clients are different,

01:07:37.500 --> 01:07:39.500
the conditions are different,

01:07:39.500 --> 01:07:41.500
the situation is different.

01:07:41.500 --> 01:07:43.500
And if this is a sales manager

01:07:43.500 --> 01:07:45.500
who has to let go of the goods,

01:07:45.500 --> 01:07:47.500
the buyer who came

01:07:47.500 --> 01:07:49.500
and asked for the goods,

01:07:49.500 --> 01:07:51.500
well, probably the decisions

01:07:51.500 --> 01:07:53.500
are not very good here,

01:07:53.500 --> 01:07:55.500
and therefore making independent decisions

01:07:55.500 --> 01:07:57.500
is not very good.

01:07:57.500 --> 01:07:59.500
On the other hand,

01:07:59.500 --> 01:08:01.500
the importance of the factor for the organization

01:08:01.500 --> 01:08:03.500
and the weight of the factor in these positions

01:08:03.500 --> 01:08:05.500
gives us a total weight for each position,

01:08:05.500 --> 01:08:07.500
according to which we determine

01:08:07.500 --> 01:08:09.500
its position on our grid.

01:08:09.500 --> 01:08:11.500
Thus, we determine

01:08:11.500 --> 01:08:13.500
the weight for each position

01:08:13.500 --> 01:08:15.500
or grade for our organization.

01:08:15.500 --> 01:08:17.500
How many of them we lead

01:08:17.500 --> 01:08:19.500
is, in general, a matter of our will

01:08:19.500 --> 01:08:21.500
and understanding of the situation.

01:08:21.500 --> 01:08:23.500
Not much is known about

01:08:23.500 --> 01:08:25.500
the number of positions,

01:08:25.500 --> 01:08:27.500
but it is desirable not to be too few.

01:08:27.500 --> 01:08:29.500
And after that,

01:08:29.500 --> 01:08:31.500
having broken

01:08:31.500 --> 01:08:33.500
our positions

01:08:33.500 --> 01:08:35.500
by grades,

01:08:35.500 --> 01:08:37.500
we bind them

01:08:37.500 --> 01:08:39.500
to the tariff grid.

01:08:39.500 --> 01:08:41.500
That is, for each of the grades

01:08:41.500 --> 01:08:43.500
we determine the upper and lower

01:08:43.500 --> 01:08:45.500
salary range, as well as the median,

01:08:45.500 --> 01:08:47.500
or rather, the median,

01:08:47.500 --> 01:08:49.500
from which the upper and lower range

01:08:49.500 --> 01:08:51.500
of the level of labor payment

01:08:51.500 --> 01:08:53.500
will be received.

01:08:53.500 --> 01:08:55.500
This is a rather long, complex

01:08:55.500 --> 01:08:57.500
and labor-intensive system.

01:08:57.500 --> 01:08:59.500
Let's consider it

01:08:59.500 --> 01:09:01.500
using the example of the HE method,

01:09:01.500 --> 01:09:03.500
which I just mentioned.

01:09:03.500 --> 01:09:05.500
Here is the binary-factor method.

01:09:05.500 --> 01:09:07.500
What factors can be present here?

01:09:07.500 --> 01:09:09.500
Let's assume

01:09:09.500 --> 01:09:11.500
the degree of authority,

01:09:11.500 --> 01:09:13.500
the scale of actions,

01:09:13.500 --> 01:09:15.500
or the turnover.

01:09:15.500 --> 01:09:17.500
What turnover

01:09:17.500 --> 01:09:19.500
does the employee

01:09:19.500 --> 01:09:21.500
have in terms of money?

01:09:21.500 --> 01:09:23.500
One can do nothing,

01:09:23.500 --> 01:09:25.500
while the other can do a lot.

01:09:25.500 --> 01:09:27.500
The degree of influence

01:09:27.500 --> 01:09:29.500
on the company's overall results

01:09:29.500 --> 01:09:31.500
is an important factor.

01:09:31.500 --> 01:09:33.500
Technical and professional knowledge

01:09:33.500 --> 01:09:35.500
of employees is very important

01:09:35.500 --> 01:09:37.500
for one company,

01:09:37.500 --> 01:09:39.500
but not for the other.

01:09:39.500 --> 01:09:41.500
Management skills.

01:09:41.500 --> 01:09:43.500
Serious, powerful management skills

01:09:43.500 --> 01:09:45.500
and competencies of a corresponding education

01:09:45.500 --> 01:09:47.500
are necessary for working in this company.

01:09:47.500 --> 01:09:49.500
The skills of the employees

01:09:49.500 --> 01:09:51.500
are important for some,

01:09:51.500 --> 01:09:53.500
but not for others.

01:09:53.500 --> 01:09:55.500
The complexity of decision-making

01:09:55.500 --> 01:09:57.500
is important for one company,

01:09:57.500 --> 01:09:59.500
but not for the other.

01:09:59.500 --> 01:10:01.500
Thus, we get an assessment

01:10:01.500 --> 01:10:03.500
of the importance of each factor

01:10:03.500 --> 01:10:05.500
for the company.

01:10:05.500 --> 01:10:07.500
How?

01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:09.500
We conduct a survey of the company's managers,

01:10:09.500 --> 01:10:11.500
sum up the results,

01:10:11.500 --> 01:10:13.500
analyze what has been achieved.

01:10:13.500 --> 01:10:15.500
It turns out that for different industries,

01:10:15.500 --> 01:10:17.500
for different sectors of the market,

01:10:17.500 --> 01:10:19.500
these weight factors

01:10:19.500 --> 01:10:21.500
can be quite different.

01:10:21.500 --> 01:10:23.500
Although there is a share of subjectivism here.

01:10:23.500 --> 01:10:25.500
But what can you do?

01:10:25.500 --> 01:10:27.500
Where is it not?

01:10:27.500 --> 01:10:29.500
The H-group method

01:10:29.500 --> 01:10:31.500
or the H-method of the guide tables

01:10:31.500 --> 01:10:33.500
includes what factors?

01:10:33.500 --> 01:10:35.500
There are only three groups of factors.

01:10:35.500 --> 01:10:37.500
These are knowledge and skills,

01:10:37.500 --> 01:10:39.500
solving problems at work,

01:10:39.500 --> 01:10:41.500
and responsibility.

